-- Notre Dame, Louisville Reach NCAA Women’s Basketball Final Four
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2013-04-03T04:51:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-03/notre-dame-louisville-reach-ncaa-women-s-basketball-final-four.html
Notre Dame  University and the
University of Louisville won to complete the Final Four lineup
at the national women’s college basketball tournament.  Notre Dame defeated second-seeded Duke 87-76 last night in
the Norfolk region and fifth-seeded Louisville defeated No. 2
Tennessee 86-78 in the Oklahoma City region.  Notre Dame will face Connecticut in a meeting of top
regional seeds on April 7 at New Orleans Arena. Louisville will
play second-seeded  California  for a place in the National
Collegiate Athletic Association championship game.  Skylar Diggins scored 24 points for the Fighting Irish
(35-1), who are going to their third consecutive Final Four.
Kayla McBride added 18 points.  Shoni Schimmel scored 24 points for the Cardinals (28-8),
who defeated the Vols two nights after beating defending
champion Baylor.  The championship game is scheduled for April 9 in  New
Orleans .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nancy Kercheval in Washington at 
